Version Vault
A GitHub/GitLab-like platform built with React.js, Node.js, Express, MongoDB, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS using a monorepo architecture with Nx.

Tech Stack

Frontend: React.js, Redux Toolkit, Vite, Tailwind CSS, TypeScript
Backend: Node.js, Express, TypeScript, TSyringe (DI), Zod
Database: MongoDB (Mongoose)
Cache: Redis (ioredis)
Monorepo: Nx
Containerization: Docker


Prerequisites
Make sure you have these installed:

Node.js >= 18
npm >= 9
Docker Desktop
Git


Project Structure
version-vault/
├── backend/        ← Node.js + Express API (Clean Architecture)
├── frontend/       ← React.js + Redux
├── packages/
│   └── shared-types/  ← Shared TypeScript types
├── docker-compose.dev.yml
└── package.json

Getting Started
1. Clone the repository
bashgit clone https://github.com/your-username/version-vault.git
cd version-vault
2. Install dependencies
bash# Install root dependencies
npm install

# Install backend dependencies
npm install --prefix backend

# Install frontend dependencies
npm install --prefix frontend
3. Setup environment variables
bash# Copy example env file and fill in your values
cp backend/.env.example backend/.env

Running with Docker (Recommended)
Start MongoDB + Redis containers
bashdocker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d
Verify containers are running
bashdocker ps
# Should show:
# version-vault-mongo   → port 27017
# version-vault-redis   → port 6379
Stop containers
bashdocker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml down

Running the Backend
bash# Navigate to backend folder
cd backend

# Development mode (with auto-reload via nodemon)
npm run dev

# Build for production
npm run build

# Run production build
npm start
Backend runs on: http://localhost:5000
Backend Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

Running the Frontend
bash# Navigate to frontend folder
cd frontend

# Development mode
npm run dev

# Build for production
npm run build

# Preview production build
npm run preview
Frontend runs on: http://localhost:5173

Running Both Together (from root)
bash# Run backend
nx serve backend

# Run frontend (in a separate terminal)
nx serve frontend

